Boards & Governance  
The SCRA Board of Trustees and its Executive Committee provide oversight and governance for SCRA's operations. The SC Launch board is an independent board tasked with approving investments and providing counsel to the SC Launch team and SC Launch companies.

to content










Board SCRA The Board of Trustees and its Executive Committee provide leadership and oversight for SCRA, its affiliates and its programs. See the Board Members 



Board SC Launch The SC Launch Board is comprised of experts with significant research, commercialization and entrepreneurial experience.  See the Board Members 







Back to Top




﻿





SCRA Board of Trustees | SCRA












 




SCRA



Menu


Search




Search terms



Submit











SCRA Board of Trustees
The SCRA Board of Trustees is drawn from leading corporate and academic organizations and economic development institutions. The Executive Committee represents the voting arm of the Board, while the larger Board of Trustees has an advisory role and counsels the Executive Committee of the actions recommended by the board, ensuring that  SCRA effectively executes its mission.

to content








SCRA Board of Trustees' Executive Committee  The Executive Committee is comprised of the Presidents of Clemson University, the Medical University of South Carolina, and the University of South Carolina at Columbia, the Governor or designee (to serve as Chairman), an additional appointee of the Governor, the Chairman of the House Ways and Means Committee or designee, the Chairman of the Senate Finance Committee or designee and two additional members. The Executive Committee has all powers and authority, serving as the voting members of the Board of Trustees. Terms of elected executive committee members are for four years, and half expire every two years. An elected executive committee member may not serve more than two consecutive four-year elected terms. 






